WEBVTT

00:02.081 --> 00:04.149
Tonight on Kitchen Nightmares...

00:04.216 --> 00:06.317
Chef Ramsay heads to music city...

00:06.418 --> 00:07.719
Nashville, Tennessee,

00:07.820 --> 00:10.755
but he is immediately forced
to deal with a sour note.

00:10.856 --> 00:12.690
What the hell are you doing?

00:12.758 --> 00:15.860
This cajun restaurant is
run by chef/owner Chappy...

00:15.961 --> 00:17.895
The guy in the big hat.

00:17.996 --> 00:19.196
Whose careless methods

00:19.297 --> 00:20.998
- have hurt his eatery...
- They hate it all.

00:21.099 --> 00:22.299
As well as his wife's confidence.

00:22.400 --> 00:24.301
Show that you care,

00:24.402 --> 00:27.470
or we have done all of this for nothing.

00:27.538 --> 00:29.272
He blames Nashville customers...

00:29.339 --> 00:32.441
- Both came back.
- That's the Nashville folks we know and love.

00:32.543 --> 00:34.577
When he should really
be taking a hard look...

00:34.679 --> 00:36.179
Oh, my God.

00:36.213 --> 00:37.580
At his less-than-appetizing food...

00:37.682 --> 00:41.017
It looks like Chappy
took a crappy in my gumbo.

00:41.118 --> 00:43.218
And his disturbing kitchen practices.

00:43.319 --> 00:45.220
See the mold on these things?

00:45.321 --> 00:47.222
And in spite of Chef Ramsay
showing him the way...

00:47.323 --> 00:48.957
You have to open your eyes.

00:49.059 --> 00:51.660
Chappy prefers his own destructive route.

00:51.761 --> 00:53.162
You don't know what the
hell you're talking about.

00:53.262 --> 00:54.963
This place should be shut down.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.799
Find out if Chef Ramsay can get through

00:56.900 --> 00:58.300
to the stubborn owner...

00:58.401 --> 01:00.634
Listen to me, something
you're not very good at doing.

01:00.703 --> 01:02.603
There's nothing wrong with my food.

01:02.705 --> 01:04.638
Or will Chappy's come crashing down?

01:09.692 --> 01:10.978
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:10.979 --> 01:13.681
What is that? You're serving rotten food.

01:13.782 --> 01:16.083
- You could possibly kill them.
- Then wake up!

01:16.184 --> 01:17.383
You wake up!

01:17.484 --> 01:19.619
- Shut the place down.
- Get out of here!

01:19.653 --> 01:21.421
That is amazing.

01:21.522 --> 01:23.223
I can't take any more.

01:23.324 --> 01:25.759
Thank you, Chef.

01:30.164 --> 01:33.999
Nashville, Tennessee, the
epicenter of country music,

01:34.101 --> 01:35.400
and home to Chappy's restaurant,

01:35.435 --> 01:39.105
a cajun eatery owned
by John "Chappy" Chapman

01:39.206 --> 01:40.940
and his wife Starr.

01:41.041 --> 01:42.174
It's ready.

01:42.242 --> 01:43.743
I started when I was about 2 1/2

01:43.844 --> 01:45.745
with my mother in the kitchen.

01:45.846 --> 01:48.579
I was the one that would
put the crabs in the pot.

01:48.680 --> 01:50.281
Aah!

01:50.382 --> 01:51.883
Thank you for coming.

01:51.984 --> 01:53.985
We opened our first
Chappy's in a little town

01:54.086 --> 01:57.421
called Long Beach, Mississippi,
in 1984. Bon appétit.

01:57.522 --> 02:01.926
And it was a huge, overnight success.

02:02.027 --> 02:03.761
But in 2005,

02:03.862 --> 02:06.964
after hurricane Katrina
destroyed the restaurant,

02:07.065 --> 02:10.901
Chappy and Starr were forced
to relocate to Nashville.

02:11.002 --> 02:12.903
Chappy, my table doesn't
like the crab cakes

02:13.004 --> 02:14.204
or the turtle soup.

02:14.305 --> 02:16.606
That's the Nashville
folks we know and love.

02:16.707 --> 02:18.642
I think people in Nashville have a problem

02:18.743 --> 02:19.976
with New Orleans cuisine.

02:20.043 --> 02:22.044
They hate it all.

02:22.146 --> 02:23.746
Oh, well. These people don't know.

02:25.883 --> 02:27.984
Fine.

02:28.085 --> 02:30.086
I definitely don't think our issue is

02:30.187 --> 02:31.788
the people of Nashville.

02:31.889 --> 02:32.922
I have to send it back.

02:33.023 --> 02:35.323
It's overcooked and it tastes fishy.

02:35.424 --> 02:39.027
- The issue is more Chappy.
- Don't argue. Move on!

02:39.128 --> 02:40.762
Chappy is extremely hard-headed.

02:40.963 --> 02:42.563
- There's nothing wrong with my food.
- Chap...

02:42.665 --> 02:44.365
Both came back.

02:44.466 --> 02:47.102
If Chappy would listen to feedback,

02:47.203 --> 02:49.204
the business would be doing much better.

02:51.807 --> 02:54.842
It's a barramundi. That's
what I need working.

02:54.943 --> 02:55.943
The menu, it's like a book.

02:56.044 --> 02:57.044
I do want to let you know

02:57.145 --> 02:58.145
about some appetizers

02:58.246 --> 02:59.246
that we're featuring tonight

02:59.347 --> 03:00.647
that are not listed.

03:00.748 --> 03:03.984
Not to mention the 15, 16
things we have to recite.

03:04.085 --> 03:05.786
We have crab cakes paneer.

03:05.887 --> 03:06.886
Swordfish piccata.

03:06.987 --> 03:07.887
We also have our blackened shrimp.

03:08.022 --> 03:09.222
Two lobster tails.

03:09.323 --> 03:10.423
They're stacked on top
of one another twice.

03:10.624 --> 03:11.925
I think that's it.

03:12.026 --> 03:14.527
- That's a lot to remember.
- I said etouffée, right?

03:14.628 --> 03:17.063
I can't see how he makes any money.

03:17.164 --> 03:18.965
We do not have the volume

03:19.066 --> 03:22.368
to be able to sell all that stuff.

03:22.469 --> 03:23.768
Chappy's definitely needs an update.

03:23.870 --> 03:26.138
It's not 1984 anymore.

03:26.206 --> 03:28.506
They called, they want
their wallpaper back.

03:30.609 --> 03:33.045
Chappy, on 120, the lady did
not like the salad dressing.

03:33.146 --> 03:34.246
What was the matter with it?

03:34.347 --> 03:36.348
She said the blue cheese
dressing is too thin.

03:36.449 --> 03:37.950
- Just get her out of here.
- Yes, Chappy.

03:38.051 --> 03:40.484
Everybody thinks they know better.

03:40.585 --> 03:42.086
So it's my job to make sure

03:42.187 --> 03:43.888
it stays the way it's supposed to be.

03:43.989 --> 03:45.589
What are y'all doing? I need to know.

03:45.724 --> 03:47.424
We're taking the prime rib off of his check

03:47.525 --> 03:49.026
'cause he didn't like
it, and he returned it.

03:49.228 --> 03:50.461
He didn't like the other one either.

03:50.528 --> 03:52.129
- He sent 'em both back, the fish too.
- John, John...

03:52.231 --> 03:53.564
For Chappy's to be saved,

03:53.665 --> 03:55.298
I think we need Chappy to change.

03:55.366 --> 03:57.267
Why waste my time?

03:57.368 --> 04:00.570
And it's not about your
pride or your experience.

04:00.671 --> 04:03.006
It's about doing what you need to do

04:03.107 --> 04:05.708
to help your business evolve
and go to the next level.

04:05.809 --> 04:07.610
I don't know what's happened.

04:07.711 --> 04:10.046
Ultimately, the success of
Chappy's relies on Chappy.

