04:54.889 --> 04:56.390
- Sure, let me go check.
- Thank you.

04:56.490 --> 04:58.091
I'll be right back.

04:59.793 --> 05:01.427
Oh. Wow, what's that?

05:01.528 --> 05:04.230
Looks like a costume that
Elton John would wear.

05:04.331 --> 05:08.567
Is that Chappy? Wow.

05:08.668 --> 05:11.670
Hey, Chappy, Chef Ramsay just got here.

05:11.771 --> 05:12.972
And before he sits, he wants to know

05:13.073 --> 05:14.573
if you have a second to chat with him.

05:14.674 --> 05:16.107
It'll be just a few minutes.

05:16.208 --> 05:17.508
Okay.

05:17.609 --> 05:20.812
- He is gonna be right out.
- Yeah. Excellent.

05:26.752 --> 05:30.855
Yeah, he's gonna be right out, he told me.

05:30.989 --> 05:32.789
Is he alone in the kitchen?
Does he have any assistants?

05:32.890 --> 05:35.092
No, he's got some back there. He's, uh...

05:35.193 --> 05:37.194
I think there's three
men back there with him.

05:37.295 --> 05:39.330
Let me go check and see
how he's doing, okay?

05:39.431 --> 05:40.530
- Yeah. Excellent.
- Mm-hmm.

05:40.631 --> 05:41.832
Thank you.

05:43.935 --> 05:45.836
- Are we getting close, Chappy?
- Yeah?

05:45.937 --> 05:47.670
Okay. He is right up in the front.

05:59.316 --> 06:02.151
Oh... dear.

06:02.252 --> 06:04.353
I'm gonna get a glass of water,

06:04.454 --> 06:05.553
then I'll go meet Darth Vader.

06:05.654 --> 06:07.356
Uh-huh.

06:09.592 --> 06:11.693
Wow. How are you?

06:11.794 --> 06:13.228
Gordon, nice to meet you.

06:13.296 --> 06:14.696
- Those pants are bright.
- I'm a hot pepper, brother.

06:14.797 --> 06:16.931
Wow, wow, wow. Throwback to the '80s?

06:17.033 --> 06:18.233
It's just something I've always worn.

06:18.334 --> 06:19.333
Wow, look at that thing there.

06:19.434 --> 06:21.835
That's when I was cute and young.

06:21.936 --> 06:23.537
- Cute and young? How long ago was that?
- You remember those days?

06:23.638 --> 06:25.572
I do. Just take me back to the beginning.

06:25.673 --> 06:28.809
- How long have you been here?
- Since June of '06.

06:28.977 --> 06:30.777
- Right. Mm-hmm.
- After Katrina.

06:30.879 --> 06:32.813
What's the comparison
between here and Mississippi?

06:32.914 --> 06:35.015
Mississippi was kind of never-ending,

06:35.116 --> 06:36.316
because it was 23 years.

06:36.417 --> 06:39.952
So it was a long time
in a successful business,

06:40.054 --> 06:41.154
- doing what I do.
- You're amazing.

06:41.255 --> 06:43.056
And here... talk me
through the first two years,

06:43.157 --> 06:47.494
- business-wise.
- Kind of a rough beginning here in Nashville.

06:47.594 --> 06:48.794
Of course, the new guys in town...

06:48.896 --> 06:50.096
- People are afraid of us.
- Mm-hmm.

06:50.197 --> 06:53.298
You know, we don't do
traditional Nashville food...

06:53.433 --> 06:55.534
burgers and pulled pork and chicken wings.

06:55.635 --> 06:56.735
We don't do that.

06:56.836 --> 06:58.337
No, we do the New Orleans food.

06:58.438 --> 07:00.639
So a lot of people were afraid.

07:00.740 --> 07:02.874
And this is what we're trying
to deal with still to this day.

07:03.015 --> 07:04.316
And here, you're taking a play

07:04.417 --> 07:07.218
- on fine dining?
- It's more like I'm taking a play

07:07.319 --> 07:10.054
on casual fine dining.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.655
- Look at those napkins.
- Yeah.

07:11.756 --> 07:12.856
Um, waiters' bow ties. I mean,

07:12.891 --> 07:14.492
it doesn't strike me as somewhat casual.

07:14.560 --> 07:16.060
I mean, it's quite formal, no?

07:16.161 --> 07:19.297
- Uh... no.
- Right. Okay.

07:19.398 --> 07:21.799
My God, I've been doing this a long time.

07:21.900 --> 07:24.634
I've eaten all over the
world. I see what people do.

07:24.735 --> 07:26.136
I don't think I'm so far off.

07:26.237 --> 07:28.771
And how would you rate your
food, currently, out of ten?

07:28.839 --> 07:30.440
- What would you give it?
- I wouldn't put it out

07:30.541 --> 07:32.976
- if I didn't think it was delicious.
- Just asking.

07:33.077 --> 07:34.277
So I give 'em a ten every
time I do it, you know.

07:34.378 --> 07:35.479
Okay. Well, let me sit down,

07:35.513 --> 07:36.980
have a little run at the menu,

07:37.081 --> 07:39.415
- and get up to speed with your style of cooking.
- Okay.

07:39.516 --> 07:41.817
- Thank you. Yes.
- I think they have a table over there for you.

07:41.918 --> 07:44.253
I think my food is the
best New Orleans cuisine

07:44.321 --> 07:45.721
in Nashville, hands down.

07:45.822 --> 07:49.558
So I can't figure out why
people haven't come enjoyed.

07:49.659 --> 07:51.360
All right.

07:51.461 --> 07:53.895
I was gonna put my Chappy hat on.

07:53.997 --> 07:55.497
We actually get a lot
of people that do that.

07:55.598 --> 07:57.599
- Do you?
- Uh-huh.

07:57.699 --> 07:58.833
- Little chappies.
- Right.

07:58.900 --> 08:01.636
Okay, so this is our
lunch selection right here.

08:01.737 --> 08:03.538
- Thank you. Wow, this is a big lunch menu.
- Mm-hmm. Yeah.

08:03.639 --> 08:04.739
Dinner menu's even larger.

08:04.840 --> 08:07.342
- Wow, wow, wow. Thank you.
- Absolutely.

08:07.443 --> 08:09.377
Wow.

08:09.478 --> 08:10.778
Hello. How are you?

08:10.879 --> 08:12.479
- Fantastic. And yourself?
- I'm so happy to be here.

08:12.580 --> 08:13.980
Welcome to Chappy's. My name is T.J.

08:14.081 --> 08:15.182
- Nice to meet you. T.J.
- Good to see you.

08:15.283 --> 08:18.318
- We have, like, ten different specials.
- What?

08:18.419 --> 08:20.120
As well as five different appetizers.

08:20.221 --> 08:23.323
- 15 specials?
- Yes.

08:23.424 --> 08:25.159
On top of this?

08:25.260 --> 08:26.660
Yeah. And they change every day?

08:26.761 --> 08:27.960
That's a lot to take in.

08:28.061 --> 08:29.995
No, actually, it stays exactly the same.

08:30.063 --> 08:32.097
Ah. They've been the
same since I've been here.

08:32.198 --> 08:36.001
Wow. So you know this $8.95 crawfish?

08:36.102 --> 08:38.203
I saw it's on there twice.
It's the same on the lunch menu

08:38.304 --> 08:39.238
as it is on the dinner menu.

08:39.339 --> 08:40.539
- Yeah.
- Only the price changes.

08:40.640 --> 08:43.575
So for the lunch menu, the
crawfish etouffée is $8.95.

08:43.643 --> 08:44.842
How much is it for dinner on the special?

08:44.943 --> 08:45.877
Uh, $29.95.

08:45.978 --> 08:48.280
So it jumps $20. And what changes?

08:48.381 --> 08:51.583
Nothing.

08:51.684 --> 08:53.918
T.J., come on.

08:54.019 --> 08:57.322
Your price jumps 3 1/2 times
for the special on the dinner,

08:57.423 --> 08:58.823
and nothing changes?

08:58.924 --> 09:00.558
You don't even throw me an
extra couple of tails in there?

09:00.659 --> 09:02.459
Shame on you, T.J.

09:02.494 --> 09:04.461
Well, not me. I...

09:04.563 --> 09:05.762
Is that just for the... crawfish,

09:05.863 --> 09:07.064
or is that for all the specials?

09:07.199 --> 09:08.799
It pretty much... it's pretty standard.

09:08.900 --> 09:11.402
Wow.

09:11.503 --> 09:13.504
So let's start off with, please,

09:13.605 --> 09:15.005
- the fried green tomatoes, please.
- Okay.

09:15.139 --> 09:17.740
- The chicken and sausage gumbo as well, please.
- Okay.

09:17.841 --> 09:20.343
And I'll go for that
steak and lobster rocket.

09:20.444 --> 09:21.444
Very good.

09:21.545 --> 09:24.080
Thank you. Wow.

09:24.181 --> 09:26.583
- Fried green tomatoes.
- Thank you.

09:26.684 --> 09:28.484
- What?
- Fried green.

09:28.586 --> 09:33.121
The rest of his order is going in now.

09:33.223 --> 09:34.856
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

09:34.924 --> 09:36.425
- How are you?
- I'm fine, I think. How are you?

09:36.526 --> 09:37.759
Nice to meet you. Starr Chapman.

09:37.860 --> 09:39.461
Starr, nice to see you.
Please, take a seat.

09:39.562 --> 09:41.362
- Well, welcome.
- Thank you. I'm happy to be here.

09:41.463 --> 09:43.163
- My first time in Nashville.
- Really? How do you like it?

09:43.265 --> 09:44.699
Yeah, wonderful, thank you.

09:44.799 --> 09:46.800
- We're happy to have you.
- Are you involved with the business daily?

09:46.901 --> 09:49.203
- Always. Yes, hands on.
- Oh, really?

09:49.304 --> 09:52.340
- I work the front of the house, I work the office.
- Wow.

09:52.441 --> 09:54.542
- I wear many hats. Have to.
- Uh-huh.

09:54.643 --> 09:56.544
And your husband, of course, Chappy.

09:56.645 --> 09:57.944
How long have you been together?

09:58.045 --> 09:59.279
- 29 years.
- 29 years.

09:59.380 --> 10:01.981
- Yes, sir.
- Does he listen to your input?

10:02.015 --> 10:04.684
- Not always.
- Not always. Why?

10:04.785 --> 10:05.885
Because he's a hard-headed man.

10:05.986 --> 10:09.122
I think he's set in his ways.

10:09.156 --> 10:11.023
But when it's not working, you'd adapt.

10:11.125 --> 10:13.626
Exactly. Looking at our menu,

10:13.727 --> 10:15.461
I think it's too big.

10:15.562 --> 10:16.962
I think it needs to be downsized.

10:17.063 --> 10:19.064
It's too much.

10:19.165 --> 10:20.766
You've gotta be able to adapt and change.

10:20.867 --> 10:22.701
It seems like you've hit a wall.

10:22.802 --> 10:25.103
Absolutely. That's why you're here.

10:25.204 --> 10:27.906
- Mm-hmm.
- I think that's gonna be the key.

10:28.007 --> 10:30.441
I believe Chef Ramsay is the only person

10:30.542 --> 10:31.743
who could turn Chappy around.

10:31.843 --> 10:36.581
For me, it's like trying to blow
air into a balloon with a hole in it.

10:36.682 --> 10:38.683
All right, the fried
green tomato appetizer.

10:38.784 --> 10:40.985
Mm-hmm. Is that parmesan on there?

10:41.086 --> 10:43.488
It is. And crawfish tails
and hollandaise sauce.

10:43.622 --> 10:44.522
- Thanks, T.J.
- You're welcome.

10:44.623 --> 10:45.722
I'm dying to taste these

10:45.823 --> 10:46.823
- fried green tomatoes.
- Okay, good.

10:46.924 --> 10:49.025
- Well, enjoy. Bon appétit.
- Thank you.

10:49.126 --> 10:50.527
Oh, how would you rate
the food, by the way?

10:50.662 --> 10:51.961
- Excellent.
- Excellent.

10:52.062 --> 10:53.764
I just think it needs to be modernized,

10:53.864 --> 10:57.867
revamped, and "shhhp" the menu.

11:01.205 --> 11:03.205
She says it's excellent,

11:03.307 --> 11:05.408
and yet it needs to be
modernized and revamped.

11:05.542 --> 11:07.242
That doesn't sound like excellent.

11:07.344 --> 11:08.644
Because surely, if it was excellent,

11:08.745 --> 11:10.045
you wouldn't have to
do any of those things.

11:13.983 --> 11:16.619
It's bland.

11:16.687 --> 11:19.086
All right, what'd we think
of the fried green tomatoes?

11:19.188 --> 11:20.722
Uh, yeah, bland.

11:20.823 --> 11:22.424
That hollandaise sauce is almost just like

11:22.525 --> 11:24.125
a sort of... a melted butter.

11:24.226 --> 11:26.728
- Yeah, it doesn't even taste of anything.
- Sorry about that.

11:26.829 --> 11:28.763
Not your fault.

11:28.864 --> 11:30.865
Right. Next up would be the
chicken and sausage gumbo.

11:30.966 --> 11:33.967
- Gumbo? Thank you.
- You're very welcome.

11:37.905 --> 11:40.607
He said your hollandaise
sauce was extremely bland.

11:40.742 --> 11:44.244
It just tastes like a strong butter sauce.

11:44.346 --> 11:46.347
It's very good.

11:46.448 --> 11:48.349
When we bring a dish back to the kitchen,

