in front of your staff.

16:19.469 --> 16:22.371
You're a joke.

16:22.472 --> 16:23.406
The food was disgusting.

16:23.507 --> 16:25.908
- Everything was off?
- Everything.

16:26.009 --> 16:27.809
And that's without factoring in the prices.

16:27.910 --> 16:30.211
Going through each and every dish,

16:30.312 --> 16:32.547
there was a... a consistent pattern.

16:32.648 --> 16:36.350
It's like you've shut
shop up and gone home.

16:36.452 --> 16:40.988
Chappy is not very happy.

16:41.089 --> 16:43.391
- Are you done?
- With what?

16:43.491 --> 16:45.626
- Just cooking in general.
- No.

16:45.727 --> 16:48.629
- That's you at your best?
- Pardon?

16:48.730 --> 16:52.131
- That's you at your best?
- Kind of.

16:52.232 --> 16:53.766
Really?

16:53.867 --> 16:58.170
Uh, I've toned down some
spices for Nashville.

16:58.271 --> 17:00.706
When we first opened, people
complained on everything.

17:00.908 --> 17:03.409
- Too salty, too spicy.
- Too much heat.

17:03.510 --> 17:05.010
I'm not looking for excuses.

17:05.111 --> 17:07.546
Well, I
-... I... you know, what can I say?

17:07.646 --> 17:09.548
You asked me to help,
but I'm not gonna sit here

17:09.648 --> 17:11.450
and blow smoke up your asses
and say the food was amazing.

17:11.550 --> 17:14.886
I don't want you to blow
anything up my whatever,

17:14.987 --> 17:17.188
so let's not go here and go through this.

17:17.289 --> 17:18.589
You've said your piece, let's move on.

17:18.790 --> 17:20.892
You've given up.

17:20.893 --> 17:22.103
Given up what?

17:22.929 --> 17:24.528
Okay, I'm gonna go get some fresh air.

17:24.628 --> 17:26.029
Me too.

17:27.332 --> 17:28.432
Okay.

17:28.532 --> 17:30.367
Wow.

17:39.310 --> 17:41.344
Tom, order up.

17:41.411 --> 17:42.912
Uh, Mark, how does the line work?

17:43.013 --> 17:44.948
- Fry cook...
- Fry cook. Who's frying tonight?

17:45.048 --> 17:46.449
- Grill.
- Chappy.

17:46.550 --> 17:48.050
- I'm frying tonight.
- Okay, great.

17:49.753 --> 17:51.588
Oysters. Wow.

17:51.689 --> 17:54.090
- Chappy, do they stay out like that?
- _

17:54.124 --> 17:55.048
You are kidding me, aren't you?

17:55.049 --> 17:56.172
_

17:56.173 --> 17:58.147
_

17:58.149 --> 17:59.928
Wow.

18:00.229 --> 18:01.286
_

18:02.331 --> 18:03.732
Listen, I'm not that dumb.

18:03.833 --> 18:05.433
- Now you just put ice in there to chill the temperature.
- I know.

18:05.535 --> 18:07.068
"Throw some ice in, I'll check it.

18:07.169 --> 18:09.471
I want to look good."

18:12.073 --> 18:13.407
All right, now we got the first ticket.

18:13.509 --> 18:16.711
We got a grilled grouper working.

18:16.812 --> 18:18.813
Chappy, you fry the grouper with the beef?

18:18.914 --> 18:20.948
- We blacken everything in the same pan.
- Yes.

18:21.049 --> 18:23.117
What happens if the customer
was was a pescatarian?

18:23.251 --> 18:25.653
- A pescatarian?
- Yeah, they only eat fish.

18:25.854 --> 18:28.254
And they don't expect to eat
their fish with meat juices.

18:28.355 --> 18:29.990
I've never heard of one,
to tell you the truth.

18:30.090 --> 18:33.092
My God.

18:34.595 --> 18:36.329
Wow. I can't believe that's going out.

18:36.430 --> 18:38.732
Uh, Tom, take me to that table.

18:40.635 --> 18:41.935
Thank you. Sorry for interrupting.

18:42.036 --> 18:43.769
- Are you a pescatarian?
- I am.

18:43.870 --> 18:44.870
Can I borrow you for two seconds?

18:44.971 --> 18:47.472
- Would you mind? Thank you.
- Sure. Yeah.

18:47.574 --> 18:48.507
Chappy, have you got two seconds?

18:48.675 --> 18:50.876
- This is one of your customers.
- Really?

18:50.977 --> 18:52.110
Let me explain something really important,

18:52.211 --> 18:53.045
'cause I'm not [Bleep] around now.

18:53.112 --> 18:54.312
This lady is a pescatarian.

18:54.414 --> 18:56.615
Strictly fish. What I'm trying to explain,

18:56.716 --> 18:58.751
'cause you're not
listening, is that her fish

18:58.852 --> 19:00.451
was cooked in there along with the beef.

19:00.553 --> 19:02.053
It's not a general practice.

19:02.087 --> 19:03.555
It's just something you never do.

19:03.656 --> 19:04.956
It's the golden rule, but
he's totally oblivious.

19:05.057 --> 19:07.692
- Do you get sick on meat?
- Oh, very.

19:07.793 --> 19:09.994
I'm sorry.

19:10.095 --> 19:13.932
I'll make sure that's in a pan
of its own, as it should be,

19:14.033 --> 19:15.232
and cooked properly. Okay? My apologies.

19:15.434 --> 19:17.434
- I appreciate that.
- Thank you.

19:17.535 --> 19:20.336
It's cooked in the same stuff
that the meat's been cooked in.

19:20.438 --> 19:21.672
Ooh!

19:21.773 --> 19:22.773
Oh, my gosh.

19:22.874 --> 19:25.375
And it's disgusting back there.

19:25.476 --> 19:29.312
Why is... ugh.

19:29.413 --> 19:32.114
Why is the mayonnaise that color?

19:34.117 --> 19:35.952
I thought that was a jar of mustard.

19:36.053 --> 19:38.854
What's the date on this?

19:38.956 --> 19:43.092
"Sell by 27 February 2010."

19:43.193 --> 19:46.996
Expired three years ago. My God.

19:47.097 --> 19:49.497
What's that?

19:52.534 --> 19:55.036
How old is that?

19:55.137 --> 19:57.973
Raw beef and cooked beef.

19:58.074 --> 20:00.475
I cannot believe what I'm seeing.

20:00.576 --> 20:03.277
As I always say, everything
you need to know about a chef

20:03.378 --> 20:04.578
is in his fridge.

20:04.679 --> 20:07.815
Shrimp. They're stuck there.

20:07.916 --> 20:11.418
Sad. Absolutely stinking.

20:11.519 --> 20:16.456
Oh, my God. Look at that.

20:16.557 --> 20:18.258
What in the [Bleep] is that?

20:18.459 --> 20:20.693
There's a shrimp hanging
down. That's all mold.

20:20.794 --> 20:22.996
Unbelievable. Bloody hell.

20:29.366 --> 20:30.766
It's dinner service at Chappy's,

20:30.867 --> 20:33.169
and Chef Ramsay has just
made a shocking discovery...

20:33.270 --> 20:35.305
Oh, my God. That's all mold.

20:35.406 --> 20:36.839
Bloody hell.

20:36.907 --> 20:39.008
What may be the filthiest fridge

20:39.110 --> 20:40.110
he has ever seen.

20:40.244 --> 20:43.346
What a mess.

20:43.447 --> 20:45.547
- Do you have a minute? Urgently, please.
- Yes, sir.

20:45.648 --> 20:46.648
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

20:46.749 --> 20:50.285
Chappy, can I have you
for a minute, please?

20:50.386 --> 20:53.088
This fridge is an absolute mess.

20:53.189 --> 20:55.690
I have never seen that, ever!

20:55.791 --> 20:58.927
Now, I want to know what
the hell are you doing?

20:59.129 --> 21:00.928
Something must have spilled.

21:01.029 --> 21:02.830
Something must have spilled?

21:02.931 --> 21:05.266
Can you stop [Bleep] for once

21:05.367 --> 21:07.168
and just try to get real?

21:07.269 --> 21:09.870
When are these from, just out of interest?

21:09.971 --> 21:12.406
- Those are fresh potatoes.
- They are fresh today?

21:12.508 --> 21:13.707
No, they're not fresh today.

21:13.808 --> 21:16.110
Oh, my good God.

21:16.210 --> 21:17.910
Just touch that. What is that?

21:18.012 --> 21:19.646
It's warm.

21:19.747 --> 21:21.981
Have you any idea what happens to sauce

21:22.049 --> 21:23.950
when it's covered and it's hot?

21:24.051 --> 21:26.085
Tomorrow morning it's what?

21:26.187 --> 21:27.687
- Sour.
- Sour. Thank you.

21:27.788 --> 21:29.088
And when is this from?

21:29.190 --> 21:31.691
- This is a cake that we...
- This is a cake.

21:31.792 --> 21:33.325
You can't even answer me now.

21:33.426 --> 21:35.528
How old is that?

21:35.629 --> 21:38.130
- I don't know.
- Oh, my good God.

21:38.231 --> 21:39.532
See the mold in these things?

21:39.666 --> 21:41.267
- Yes.
- And this one here.

21:41.368 --> 21:43.669
- Look, see that there?
- Hmm.

21:43.770 --> 21:45.371
You stop. You're not getting anything.

21:45.472 --> 21:47.573
86 it. Come here, you. Come here.

21:47.674 --> 21:50.508
- Yeah, have a look down there. What do you see?
- Mold.

21:50.609 --> 21:52.482
Mold. And you want me to let you
take something outside of here?

21:52.483 --> 21:53.105
No.

21:53.106 --> 21:54.512
- Now [Bleep] off.
- Yes, sir.

21:54.647 --> 21:57.048
Have you any idea how long

21:57.149 --> 21:59.850
a shrimp needs to stay inside a fridge

21:59.951 --> 22:02.053
to get that much mold on there?

22:02.188 --> 22:03.288
No. Is it between the...

22:03.389 --> 22:04.688
Is it between the what?

22:04.789 --> 22:05.689
I don't know what it is, where it was.

22:05.790 --> 22:08.792
All night, you're just deflecting.

22:08.893 --> 22:12.229
How about some form of honesty?

22:12.330 --> 22:14.531
He needs some help, obviously.

22:14.632 --> 22:15.532
He needs some help?

22:15.633 --> 22:18.068
- Are you serious?
- I'm very serious about...

22:18.169 --> 22:20.836
You are one foot away from
that [Bleep] down there.

22:20.870 --> 22:23.872
- Which he obviously didn't know was down there.
- What?

22:23.973 --> 22:26.008
Well, do you think he would
have let it stay down there

22:26.109 --> 22:27.310
if he knew it was there?

22:27.411 --> 22:29.512
- Oh, so he couldn't see it?
- Obviously not.

22:29.613 --> 22:31.414
You have raised the bar.

22:31.515 --> 22:33.949
In fact, you, right now, are a legend.

22:34.050 --> 22:36.351
'Cause you have raised
the bar so [Bleep] high

22:36.452 --> 22:38.152
that you've taught every chef in the world

22:38.254 --> 22:39.554
how not to cook.

22:39.655 --> 22:42.591
Congratulations.

22:42.692 --> 22:44.693
I feel horrible.

22:46.195 --> 22:48.763
Seeing that fridge was beyond belief.

22:48.931 --> 22:50.432
I could not believe it.

22:50.533 --> 22:55.569
I had no idea. I just am speechless.

22:55.670 --> 22:59.072
Starr, you and me for a second.

22:59.173 --> 23:00.974
What is going on?

23:01.075 --> 23:02.276
I have no idea.

23:02.377 --> 23:03.711
I don't go in the walk-in cooler.

23:03.811 --> 23:06.313
I don't manage it. It's not my territory.

23:06.414 --> 23:08.615
I never even thought to look in it.

23:08.716 --> 23:12.552
I am mortified. I am embarrassed by that.

23:12.753 --> 23:14.654
You've got every right
to defend your husband,

23:14.755 --> 23:16.556
but I'm not here to sugarcoat.

23:16.657 --> 23:18.491
- I understand.
- And you're right to be mortified.

23:18.592 --> 23:20.192
And I don't expect you to sugarcoat it.

23:20.294 --> 23:22.194
But I need some form of understanding...

23:22.296 --> 23:24.896
you cannot perform like that.

23:24.997 --> 23:26.732
You must see the problem, surely.

23:26.832 --> 23:28.433
I surely do.

23:28.534 --> 23:30.135
What's happened to him?

23:30.236 --> 23:32.370
I don't know what's happened to him.

23:32.437 --> 23:36.173
If I knew, I could help
him work through it.

23:36.275 --> 23:40.311
I can't start to work with
someone that's given up.

23:40.412 --> 23:43.914
And right now, he's shown me everything

23:44.015 --> 23:46.116
to confirm he's done just that.

23:46.217 --> 23:49.452
And honestly, hand on heart,

23:49.553 --> 23:50.853
I think I'm too late.

23:50.954 --> 23:53.356
Oh, jeez.

23:53.457 --> 23:56.092
It doesn't seem like he cares.

23:56.193 --> 23:57.594
No, he does care.

23:57.695 --> 23:59.095
How do you know?

23:59.196 --> 24:01.798
I don't know. Let me go talk to him.

24:06.736 --> 24:08.537
What changed?

24:08.638 --> 24:10.773
What changed him

24:10.873 --> 24:13.875
from being so passionate and energetic

24:13.976 --> 24:16.378
into almost apathetic?

24:16.479 --> 24:18.614
I love you too.

24:26.054 --> 24:27.755
I know I'm ready, and whatever it takes,

24:27.856 --> 24:30.958
Chappy's gonna have to come up and meet me,

24:31.059 --> 24:32.493
and let's do this together.

24:32.594 --> 24:35.895
Wow.

24:37.097 --> 24:39.433
[Bleep] hell.

24:41.336 --> 24:43.737
- I'm totally mortified and embarrassed.
- I know.

24:43.838 --> 24:46.072
So show some life.

24:46.173 --> 24:48.375
Show that you care.

24:48.476 --> 24:50.877
Or we have done all of this for nothing.

24:51.078 --> 24:52.578
I know.

24:57.718 --> 25:00.018
I think Chef Ramsay nailed it.

25:00.119 --> 25:03.856
And I feel a little let down.

25:04.441 --> 25:06.119
_

25:06.120 --> 25:08.866
_

25:19.822 --> 25:22.256
At last night's dinner service,

25:22.357 --> 25:25.359
Chef Ramsay was horrified
at the bad practices.

25:25.460 --> 25:26.861
Sit down, please.

25:26.962 --> 25:28.863
This morning, he has gathered the staff

25:28.964 --> 25:31.700
to see if he can uncover
any other major issues

25:31.801 --> 25:33.401
with the restaurant.

25:33.502 --> 25:35.136
You know, I came here to help.

25:35.204 --> 25:37.338
But my biggest concern right now is Chappy.

25:37.439 --> 25:39.940
- Mm-hmm.
- I can't think of a more dangerous job.

25:40.041 --> 25:42.843
When you've got an owner at
the helm that doesn't care.

25:42.944 --> 25:44.178
Have you ever tried to talk to him?

25:44.279 --> 25:46.180
You even bother to ask him a question,

25:46.281 --> 25:48.683
and you are pissing him off.

25:48.783 --> 25:50.884
The other day, a guest wanted to know

25:50.985 --> 25:52.519
what was in a sauce, so I asked him.

25:52.620 --> 25:54.421
He said, "why the [Bleep]
do you want to know?"

25:54.522 --> 25:57.324
The condescending and the rudeness,

25:57.425 --> 25:59.659
and the yelling where
the customers can hear,

25:59.760 --> 26:01.361
that's really, really bad.

26:01.462 --> 26:04.163
I feel like I always get yelled at a lot,

26:04.265 --> 26:05.765
just for everything.

26:05.866 --> 26:08.601
He shuts you down, snaps at you.

26:08.702 --> 26:10.302
You're not even allowed to speak to him

26:10.403 --> 26:11.503
until he speaks to you.

26:11.605 --> 26:13.004
Is he always that condescending?

26:13.106 --> 26:14.540
- Absolutely.
- Yes. Yes.

26:14.641 --> 26:16.342
He always think everybody's
after... he thinks the waiters,

26:16.443 --> 26:18.344
all we care about is our
money, and nothing else.

26:18.445 --> 26:20.045
Everybody's stealing from him.

26:20.146 --> 26:21.980
- Everybody's against him?
- Everybody!

26:22.081 --> 26:24.282
What's it like dealing with
complaints in the kitchen?

26:24.383 --> 26:25.883
He usually gets upset.

26:25.984 --> 26:27.485
He gets angry.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.520
"There's nothing wrong
with this." He'll taste it.

26:29.622 --> 26:32.123
He blames everything on us or the guests.

26:32.224 --> 26:34.325
- Give me an example.
- I had a coconut cake

26:34.426 --> 26:36.026
that was returned to me. I
brought it back to Chappy.

26:36.128 --> 26:39.063
- He dug it out of the trashcan...
- What?

26:39.164 --> 26:41.064
Went back and asked the
guy what was wrong with it.

26:41.165 --> 26:43.567
From the trash? Not good.

26:43.668 --> 26:45.201
Is he different now that I'm here?

26:45.303 --> 26:46.803
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Definitely.

26:46.904 --> 26:48.204
- In what way?
- He's calmer.

26:48.306 --> 26:49.506
- He's calmer.
- He's calmer, yeah.

26:49.607 --> 26:51.141
I appreciate everybody's honesty.

26:51.208 --> 26:54.544
This is about getting
better, let me tell you.

26:54.579 --> 26:57.346
So as difficult as it may be on you

26:57.447 --> 27:02.485
to say what you've said to
me... to the man himself.

27:02.586 --> 27:03.986
No matter what happens, I've got your back.

27:04.087 --> 27:06.822
So be confident, be honest.

27:06.923 --> 27:08.724
For me to tell Chappy what I'm feeling

27:08.825 --> 27:11.927
and what's been going on,
it's definitely nerve-racking.

27:12.028 --> 27:13.127
Here they are.

27:13.228 --> 27:14.562
I don't know what he's gonna do.

27:14.664 --> 27:15.664
I don't know if he's gonna fire me,

27:15.765 --> 27:17.064
or how he's gonna accept it.

27:17.166 --> 27:19.668
Chappy's usually a person
who flies off the handle.

27:19.769 --> 27:21.703
They have some things to say.

27:21.804 --> 27:24.806
Susan, kick it off, please.

27:24.907 --> 27:26.641
The main thing, Chappy,
is just communicating,

27:26.709 --> 27:28.509
so we're on the same page.

27:28.643 --> 27:29.743
Russ.

27:29.844 --> 27:33.547
I want to preface what I have to say

27:33.648 --> 27:35.148
to both of you... I love you both.

27:35.249 --> 27:36.483
I love this restaurant.

27:36.584 --> 27:38.385
Russell, I love the love.

27:38.486 --> 27:40.987
Please tell me. Please tell me.

27:41.088 --> 27:47.727
Chappy, you're condescending,
you're rude, and you're abusive.

27:47.828 --> 27:50.530
Everybody feels it. I don't
think anybody wants to say it.

27:50.664 --> 27:52.665
And many times you lose your temper,

27:52.766 --> 27:55.368
and customers can hear you.

27:55.469 --> 27:58.371
It's hard for us to work in that condition.

27:58.472 --> 28:00.005
It seems to me as though

28:00.106 --> 28:02.607
you don't give a [Bleep]
about us as a team out here.

28:02.709 --> 28:05.510
That you think we're all against you,

28:05.611 --> 28:07.045
and that we don't have your back.

28:07.146 --> 28:09.280
And I want you to know
that we do have your back.

28:09.449 --> 28:11.650
We would love to have
some support back from you.

28:11.751 --> 28:13.852
It's just hard that you don't trust anyone.

28:13.953 --> 28:17.788
If you don't trust your staff,
then don't [Bleep] hire 'em.

28:17.889 --> 28:19.790
- Derek.
- When I first started working,

28:19.891 --> 28:21.925
I was selling the blackened
redfish to everybody.

28:22.026 --> 28:24.928
But I found out later that it was swai.

28:25.029 --> 28:27.431
And ethically, as a
server, you're asking me

28:27.532 --> 28:30.000
to go out and lie to
these people every night.

28:30.068 --> 28:32.969
- Is that true?
- It's true.

28:33.170 --> 28:34.170
And, you know, it's just not right.

28:34.271 --> 28:35.805
Why'd you do that?

28:35.906 --> 28:37.206
Why'd you swap that fish out and put...

28:37.307 --> 28:39.208
- I was trying to substitute.
- No, stop, stop, stop.

28:39.309 --> 28:40.410
Being dishonest with customers

28:40.511 --> 28:42.345
and putting them in the firing line...

28:42.413 --> 28:45.849
If he gets called out, it's your doing.

28:45.949 --> 28:47.450
I just wish he would, like,
listen to us a little bit.

28:47.551 --> 28:49.852
Anytime I've brought up an idea

28:49.952 --> 28:51.387
or even try to ask you a question,

28:51.488 --> 28:52.788
I'm wasting your time.

28:52.889 --> 28:54.490
Whoa. I try to have your back.

28:54.591 --> 28:56.091
You're fantastic.

28:56.192 --> 29:01.363
I'm directing this more towards Chappy.

29:04.066 --> 29:07.402
A lot of things have to change.

29:07.436 --> 29:10.304
I appreciate everything you say.

29:10.406 --> 29:13.240
And you're right on target.

29:13.341 --> 29:15.142
Chappy...

29:15.243 --> 29:17.545
do you find this kind of feedback

29:17.646 --> 29:19.580
from your team helpful?

29:25.286 --> 29:27.821
I do.

29:27.922 --> 29:29.222
It does get tough.

29:29.323 --> 29:32.225
And if I was negative to
you of a personal event,

29:32.326 --> 29:34.027
apologize. It wasn't meant to hurt.

29:34.128 --> 29:37.062
Sometimes I get off the edge too.

29:37.163 --> 29:39.865
I'm so blessed that this has happened,

29:39.966 --> 29:42.668
because nothing was gonna
change unless we went

29:42.769 --> 29:44.702
all the way down there,
put the light on it,

29:44.804 --> 29:51.043
looked at it and said,
"whoa! Let's fix this."

29:51.144 --> 29:53.645
We have slacked off for quite some time,

29:53.746 --> 29:57.149
but we'll get back to it.

29:57.250 --> 29:59.584
I hope Chappy can change.

29:59.685 --> 30:00.784
I know sometimes they say you can't

30:00.885 --> 30:02.886
teach an old dog new tricks,

30:02.988 --> 30:05.489
but I'm hoping that you can.

30:05.623 --> 30:08.725
Chef Ramsay still remains unconvinced

30:08.827 --> 30:11.028
that Chappy has seen the error of his ways.

30:11.129 --> 30:14.265
Sir, have you heard of
the restaurant Chappy's?

30:14.366 --> 30:16.466
So he has provided Chappy and
Starr with a fully equipped

30:16.567 --> 30:18.501
stakeout vehicle, so they can monitor

30:18.569 --> 30:20.170
his interaction with the locals.

30:20.271 --> 30:22.705
Hello. How are you?

30:22.806 --> 30:24.507
Nice to see you. You like cajun?

30:24.608 --> 30:26.909
- We love cajun.
- Have you heard of Chappy's?

30:27.011 --> 30:27.910
- Yes.
- You have heard of Chappy's?

30:28.012 --> 30:29.145
- Yes, we have.
- Good.

30:29.246 --> 30:30.246
Have you been there?

30:30.348 --> 30:31.948
- Yes, a couple of times.
- We have been.

30:32.048 --> 30:34.850
A couple of times. Tell
me the experience, please.

30:34.985 --> 30:37.186
Big on show. Very... wants to spend

30:37.287 --> 30:39.188
all his time and money
on promoting himself.

30:39.289 --> 30:40.990
We had the etouffée when we went

30:41.091 --> 30:43.825
and probably one of the
worst dishes you've had?

30:43.926 --> 30:44.826
Yeah, it tasted a little burnt.

30:44.927 --> 30:46.128
A little bit burnt. Wow.

30:46.229 --> 30:47.329
- I appreciate your honesty.
- Absolutely.

30:47.430 --> 30:49.930
- Thank you, my darling.
- Thank you so much.

30:50.032 --> 30:51.532
Have you heard of Chappy's, the restaurant?

30:51.666 --> 30:52.766
You haven't heard of it. Thank you.

30:52.868 --> 30:54.568
How are you? Have you heard of Chappy's?

30:54.636 --> 30:56.170
- I have.
- Good. Good, good, good.

30:56.171 --> 30:58.072
- Have you been to Chappy's?
- I have been.

30:58.173 --> 30:59.507
I didn't feel it was real authentic cajun.

30:59.574 --> 31:01.309
Looking for etouffée and andouille

31:01.310 --> 31:02.310
and good oysters and shrimp.

31:02.411 --> 31:03.777
Simple stuff, spicy.

31:04.012 --> 31:05.078
They have that kind of food there.

31:05.213 --> 31:06.513
Did you try it?

31:06.870 --> 31:08.390
What I tried was not great.

31:09.817 --> 31:12.019
I eat better cajun food
on the cajun food truck

31:12.120 --> 31:14.154
that rolls around.

31:14.255 --> 31:15.555
The food quality is sub par,

31:18.759 --> 31:21.494
I wouldn't mind to pay $30
to $40 for a good entrée

31:21.594 --> 31:23.295
but it wasn't good.

31:23.397 --> 31:25.197
It's not authentic cajun.

31:25.298 --> 31:27.099
Bad food, bad atmosphere.

31:27.200 --> 31:30.136
- Really?
- Bad hat.

31:30.237 --> 31:31.237
I'm here to help fix that restaurant.

31:31.338 --> 31:32.738
- Will you bear with me...
- Yes.

31:32.839 --> 31:33.939
- And give it one more shot?
- Yes.

31:34.041 --> 31:36.441
- I appreciate it. Thank you.
- Thanks.

31:36.575 --> 31:38.476
Bye-bye.

31:43.815 --> 31:45.716
Okay, were you listening?

31:45.817 --> 31:47.118
- Absolutely.
- Yeah.

31:47.219 --> 31:48.520
Tough to watch.

31:48.620 --> 31:50.321
I agree. It is tough to watch.

31:50.423 --> 31:52.656
You think you're doing
something that they want,

31:52.690 --> 31:54.658
and then they don't.

31:54.759 --> 31:56.060
So it's a good eye-awakening,

31:56.161 --> 31:58.995
an epiphany of what we need to do.

31:59.097 --> 32:00.730
Less show, more quality.

32:00.798 --> 32:03.934
- Absolutely.
- That's... that's... in a nutshell.

32:04.001 --> 32:05.802
Time to move forward. Agreed?

32:05.903 --> 32:07.637
- Agreed.
- Agreed.

32:07.738 --> 32:09.338
Well, when you hear people
talking on the street,

32:09.440 --> 32:10.639
and they don't see you listening,

32:10.740 --> 32:12.442
they'll say things that maybe

32:12.543 --> 32:13.543
they wouldn't say in front of you.

32:13.643 --> 32:16.679
It was an eye-opener.

32:16.780 --> 32:18.414
Coming up...

32:18.482 --> 32:20.383
- Chappy, listen to me.
- No.

32:20.484 --> 32:22.017
All eyes are on Chappy.

32:22.119 --> 32:24.519
I need you to step up
to the plate or go home.

32:24.620 --> 32:27.322
Will he finally lead his team
to a successful service...

32:27.423 --> 32:29.057
- How long, Chappy?
- Almost ready.

32:29.158 --> 32:31.859
Or will his customers
be disappointed again?

32:31.961 --> 32:33.861
Chappy, stop what you're doing. Stop!

32:34.063 --> 32:36.064
That's coming up on Kitchen Nightmares.

32:36.165 --> 32:38.200
That would be one pain in my ass gone.

32:46.031 --> 32:48.032
After setting Chappy, hopefully,

32:48.133 --> 32:49.233
on the path to change,

32:49.334 --> 32:52.069
Chef Ramsay and his team
work through the night

32:52.170 --> 32:54.872
on a major renovation.

32:57.909 --> 32:58.843
Good morning.

32:58.910 --> 33:00.710
Good morning.

33:00.911 --> 33:02.311
Get ready for some big changes.

33:02.412 --> 33:03.412
Let's get on with it.

33:04.514 --> 33:06.750
Please remove your blindfolds.

33:06.851 --> 33:08.251
Ah!

33:10.154 --> 33:12.155
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, man.

33:12.256 --> 33:13.489
Oh, my God.

33:13.590 --> 33:14.991
Welcome to the new Chappy's.

33:15.092 --> 33:16.992
- That's nice. Look at that.
- Awesome.

33:17.093 --> 33:19.094
How incredibly cool.

33:19.195 --> 33:22.030
Gone are those tacky, dated yellow walls.

33:22.132 --> 33:24.633
Now it's comfortable, modern.

33:24.734 --> 33:26.235
Much more warm and inviting.

33:26.335 --> 33:28.771
- Yeah.
- We got rid of a lot of the chairs

33:28.872 --> 33:30.172
and replaced them with
pews, so you get that

33:30.273 --> 33:32.173
sort of intimate, sort of family feel.

33:32.374 --> 33:34.475
So much better. I love it.

33:34.609 --> 33:36.710
- Take a look at this wall.
- Mm-hmm.

33:36.812 --> 33:39.413
We have reclaimed wood from a local bar,

33:39.514 --> 33:42.150
- and then added artistic photos.
- Uh-huh, the French Quarter.

33:42.251 --> 33:43.584
- You recognize it?
- Oh, of course.

33:43.652 --> 33:45.753
We got rid of all the
clutter from Mardi Gras,

33:45.854 --> 33:47.655
- including Miss Cleo.
- Yeah!

33:47.756 --> 33:49.289
Yeah.

33:49.356 --> 33:52.292
- It's the ambiance that Nashville wants.
- Yeah.

33:52.393 --> 33:56.096
And it still pays homage to
the home of cajun cuisine.

33:56.197 --> 33:57.330
Starr, how do you feel?

34:01.235 --> 34:03.036
- You happy, my darling?
- Absolutely.

34:03.137 --> 34:04.336
- You like it?
- Yes!

34:04.437 --> 34:05.871
Perfect.

34:05.972 --> 34:07.673
- It's absolutely perfect.
- It is absolutely stunning.

34:07.774 --> 34:10.876
I love it. Everything's so fresh.

34:10.976 --> 34:12.610
So clean, so modern.

34:12.712 --> 34:15.714
It just oozes New Orleans charm.

34:15.815 --> 34:17.817
Do we have a happy Chappy?

34:17.918 --> 34:20.150
- It's very, very nice.
- Mm-hmm.

34:20.252 --> 34:22.553
It's not my style, but
I was just gonna kinda

34:22.654 --> 34:25.255
grin, bear it, move on.

34:25.357 --> 34:26.389
Thank you, sir.

34:26.491 --> 34:28.592
Thank you.

34:28.694 --> 34:30.695
Yeah.

34:30.795 --> 34:32.763
All right, all right.

34:32.797 --> 34:35.733
Now, as big as the decor change was,

34:35.833 --> 34:37.766
the menu change is even bigger.

34:37.835 --> 34:38.936
Let's go through the
menu from top to bottom.

34:39.036 --> 34:40.237
Chef Ramsay has modernized

34:40.338 --> 34:44.875
and reduced the menu from 100 dishes to 22.

34:44.976 --> 34:46.877
First of all, that is the only page.

34:46.978 --> 34:49.646
Yes! Yes!

34:49.714 --> 34:51.815
Let's start off at the
top. Shrimp and grits,

34:51.915 --> 34:54.217
done with creole seasoning,
onions, and tomato.

34:54.318 --> 34:55.417
Delicious.

34:55.518 --> 34:57.085
Next to that,

34:57.154 --> 34:58.955
blackened redfish served with citronelle

34:59.056 --> 35:00.356
and a herb salad.

35:00.457 --> 35:02.859
And what do we do when we've
run out of redfish, Chappy?

35:02.960 --> 35:04.793
- It's 86ed.
- 86.

35:04.895 --> 35:05.895
- That's right.

35:05.996 --> 35:07.396
So don't even ask for it!

35:07.497 --> 35:10.098
Fried chicken served with apple butter.

35:10.199 --> 35:14.236
Delicious apple butter.
Absolutely delicious.

35:14.337 --> 35:17.038
Chappy, you've gone quiet.

35:17.139 --> 35:18.173
I'm thinking...

35:18.274 --> 35:20.775
how we're gonna do it.

35:20.809 --> 35:23.278
Let me tell you something.

35:23.379 --> 35:25.712
Your cooks have been here
since early this morning.

35:25.813 --> 35:27.314
They have been under the guidance

35:27.415 --> 35:29.116
of a great chef that I brought here...

35:29.217 --> 35:30.918
Chris Fox. Chris.

35:31.019 --> 35:33.153
- Good morning.
- Good morning, guys.

35:33.255 --> 35:35.189
This young man has been
cooking for over 15 years.

35:35.357 --> 35:37.424
He has the most amazing
wealth of experience.

35:37.458 --> 35:39.860
- Wonderful.
- I paid for Chris to be here

35:39.994 --> 35:41.494
to really implement these standards

35:41.595 --> 35:43.496
after I have gone.

35:43.597 --> 35:46.499
I think Chef Chris is such a blessing.

35:46.600 --> 35:48.301
Chappy's gonna get a
chance to work side by side

35:48.402 --> 35:49.936
with this gentleman.

35:50.137 --> 35:53.039
So there are no excuses. Okay?

35:53.140 --> 35:55.041
There's something else I need to bring in.

35:55.142 --> 35:57.075
- Uniforms.
- Oh, wow! Yeah!

35:58.177 --> 36:00.078
Oh, my God.

36:00.179 --> 36:03.081
The uniforms are great. Now it's casual.

36:03.182 --> 36:05.918
And this whole new image,
it's gonna be fantastic.

36:06.019 --> 36:07.719
It feels appropriate. No white shirt,

36:07.820 --> 36:09.521
no bowtie, no black pants.

36:09.622 --> 36:13.557
And, talking about pants, one more thing.

36:16.361 --> 36:19.296
When you're looking the part...

36:19.397 --> 36:20.596
There goes the party
hat and the clown pants.

36:20.697 --> 36:21.998
I love it.

36:22.099 --> 36:24.500
Listen, what I'd like you all to do now

36:24.601 --> 36:26.102
is to dig in and taste the food.

36:26.203 --> 36:28.138
Oh, my gosh.

36:28.239 --> 36:29.439
That pork chop is ridiculous.

36:29.540 --> 36:30.740
Oh, my God.

36:30.841 --> 36:32.242
There is no comparison
between Chappy's old food

36:32.343 --> 36:33.443
and Chappy's new food.

36:33.544 --> 36:35.277
The recipes are there, the flavor is there.

36:35.378 --> 36:37.579
But I'm not totally
convinced that he's happy.

36:37.680 --> 36:39.381
I think he's still, like,
got all these thoughts,

36:39.482 --> 36:40.782
like, pondering and wondering.

36:40.883 --> 36:43.118
So we'll see how that goes.

36:43.219 --> 36:45.421
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

36:53.062 --> 36:55.763
Okay, that side down. Push nice and flat.

36:55.864 --> 36:58.466
After more training on the
new menu with Chef Ramsay

36:58.500 --> 37:01.102
- and Chef Chris...
- Get it really super-charred, right?

37:01.203 --> 37:03.804
- You'll have beautiful marks. It'll look great.
- Got it.

37:03.905 --> 37:05.840
All the tools are there for Chappy

37:05.941 --> 37:07.574
to have a successful relaunch.

37:07.741 --> 37:10.643
- I think I'm gonna do the grilled Angus steak.
- Okay.

37:10.744 --> 37:11.778
Yeah, I actually want to try the crab cake.

37:11.879 --> 37:13.080
- It looks awesome.
- Crab cake?

37:13.181 --> 37:15.382
All right. Thanks, guys.

37:15.483 --> 37:18.585
Fire 114. Two pork chops, two Angus steaks.

37:18.719 --> 37:21.721
One medium, one med-rare.

37:21.822 --> 37:24.156
- Ugh!
- Uh, Chappy...

37:24.224 --> 37:26.758
- Call back, please.
- Pork chop heard.

37:26.860 --> 37:28.060
Heard. Serious, please, yeah?

37:28.161 --> 37:30.863
I got you. Chappy, Chris is expediting.

37:30.964 --> 37:33.199
He's gonna tell you what to do, just do it.

37:33.300 --> 37:35.401
How long on these steaks?

37:35.502 --> 37:37.603
- How long, Chappy?
- Almost ready.

37:37.704 --> 37:39.104
[Bleep] hell. Chris.

37:39.205 --> 37:41.039
Like, what does "almost"
mean? Like five seconds,

37:41.140 --> 37:42.540
two seconds, three seconds, one second?

37:42.641 --> 37:48.480
Give me a time, please.

37:48.580 --> 37:50.382
Chappy, I'm not asking
for the fastest kitchen,

37:50.483 --> 37:51.983
I just want a little bit of call back...

37:52.018 --> 37:53.284
"Yes, Chef, no, Chef."

37:53.386 --> 37:54.685
A little bit of liveliness
in here a little bit.

37:56.021 --> 37:57.021
[Bleep] hell.

37:57.122 --> 37:58.322
Here's your medium-rare.

37:58.423 --> 37:59.823
I needed two pork chops.

37:59.924 --> 38:01.225
Where's the pork chop, please?

38:01.326 --> 38:04.428
I need those pork chops desperately.

38:04.462 --> 38:05.962
Chappy, get in the game
a little bit, please.

38:05.997 --> 38:07.164
They're in the oven.

38:07.365 --> 38:09.166
They should have been put in
the oven a while ago, though.

38:09.267 --> 38:10.501
Yeah? They've been in.

38:10.601 --> 38:12.235
It's gotta be quicker
than that. [Bleep] me.

38:12.302 --> 38:13.903
We haven't sent anything yet.

38:14.004 --> 38:16.506
It's almost like we've gone to sleep.

38:16.606 --> 38:17.840
As Chappy struggles with the new menu,

38:17.941 --> 38:19.842
the question is is it because it's new,

38:19.943 --> 38:22.545
or is it because he's not
thrilled about serving it?

38:22.646 --> 38:24.680
I'm having such a hard time
serving a plate like that.

38:24.781 --> 38:26.115
Whatever the case may be,

38:26.183 --> 38:28.483
customers are starting to get impatient.

38:30.786 --> 38:33.522
- Let's go, I need those chops.
- We already look like jerks.

38:33.622 --> 38:35.524
- Wow.
- I need 114.

38:35.624 --> 38:37.125
I need 129.

38:37.226 --> 38:39.428
I'm also ready for 110.

38:39.562 --> 38:42.364
Oh, my God. If Chappy would listen,

38:42.465 --> 38:43.964
it would be so much better.

38:44.066 --> 38:46.267
Chappy. Chappy, listen to me.

38:46.368 --> 38:47.501
Something you're not very good at doing.

38:47.602 --> 38:49.002
Stop what you're doing. Stop!

38:57.415 --> 39:00.116
I need 114. I need 129.

39:00.217 --> 39:02.753
It's relaunch night, and
Chappy is not responding

39:02.854 --> 39:03.854
to Chef Chris.

39:03.955 --> 39:05.455
We haven't sent anything yet.

39:05.456 --> 39:07.000
_

39:06.957 --> 39:08.490
And Chef Ramsay knows

39:08.592 --> 39:11.293
he has to do something to save the service.

39:11.494 --> 39:12.494
Chappy, listen to me.

39:12.596 --> 39:14.196
Something you're not very good at doing.

39:14.297 --> 39:17.033
Come here a minute.

39:17.133 --> 39:19.435
This is it now.

39:19.536 --> 39:20.736
- I understand.
- No, no...

39:20.837 --> 39:22.971
- But if you understand, I need to hear you.
- I do.

39:23.072 --> 39:24.472
I cannot deliver any more.

39:24.574 --> 39:26.174
I need you to step up to the plate

39:26.275 --> 39:27.776
- and run your restaurant.
- Got it.

39:27.877 --> 39:28.877
Either do it or go home.

39:28.978 --> 39:30.311
- Got it.
- Let's go.

39:30.412 --> 39:33.514
Let's go.

39:33.616 --> 39:35.016
He's not good at listening, that one.

39:35.117 --> 39:36.117
Fire 110.

39:36.218 --> 39:38.251
Pork chop, shrimp and grits.

39:38.352 --> 39:41.055
Chappy, don't ignore
that ticket there, 110.

39:41.155 --> 39:42.155
[Bleep].

39:42.256 --> 39:43.657
I need those pork chops.

39:43.792 --> 39:44.892
You want me to butterfly 'em?

39:44.993 --> 39:46.794
Do not butterfly them. How long are they?

39:46.895 --> 39:47.995
Gonna be a couple minutes.

39:48.096 --> 39:49.797
At least three minutes, four minutes.

39:49.898 --> 39:53.233
I butterflied it off for you.

39:54.635 --> 39:55.935
You cannot do that!

39:56.036 --> 39:57.570
I don't want them all
butterflied like that.

39:57.638 --> 40:00.172
Those days have gone. I'm
not coming this far now

40:00.273 --> 40:01.273
to start stuffing food out.

40:01.374 --> 40:03.676
Uh, Chris, come around now, please.

40:03.777 --> 40:05.478
I don't want him bastardizing a full chop

40:05.579 --> 40:08.014
- just to get it out there.
- Yes, sir.

40:08.115 --> 40:09.615
You need to get it in the oven, okay?

40:09.716 --> 40:11.316
Guys, I got two Angus steak,
one medium-well, one medium.

40:11.417 --> 40:14.019
- 127, 128.
- 127, 128.

40:14.153 --> 40:17.155
- Excellent. Thank you.
- Make sure you're calling back, like, letting him know.

40:17.256 --> 40:20.258
I wish that Chappy would be
a little bit more open-minded

40:20.359 --> 40:21.593
to accept some of the changes.

40:21.694 --> 40:23.194
I really hope he does.

40:23.295 --> 40:25.430
[Bleep] hell.

40:25.498 --> 40:29.100
With Chef Chris switching
from expediter to head chef...

40:29.234 --> 40:30.635
Let's go. Urgently, please.

40:30.736 --> 40:32.136
Food is now making its way

40:32.237 --> 40:33.137
out to the dining room.

40:33.238 --> 40:35.239
Here's your food. Bon appétit.

40:35.340 --> 40:36.674
How hungry are you?

40:36.775 --> 40:38.275
Thank you. We love you.

40:38.376 --> 40:41.178
All the flavors complement
each other... it's very good.

40:41.279 --> 40:43.579
The mac and cheese is amazing.

40:43.681 --> 40:46.516
- Everybody's been happy with the food.
- Thank God.

40:46.617 --> 40:47.717
All your dinners are out?

40:47.818 --> 40:51.121
I got the last table.

40:51.221 --> 40:53.690
It's just wonderful.
We have a great new menu

40:53.758 --> 40:56.559
that's fresh and delivered beautifully.

40:56.661 --> 40:59.695
We just have to stick
with it, believe in it,

40:59.796 --> 41:02.297
and do everything we can to make it happen.

41:02.331 --> 41:04.900
- How are you?
- I'm okay.

41:05.001 --> 41:06.702
Everybody seemed to love everything,

41:06.803 --> 41:08.837
but I just have a hard time with it.

41:08.938 --> 41:11.439
I still think my food's great.

41:11.474 --> 41:14.142
That'll be one pain in my ass gone.

41:17.512 --> 41:21.683
Okay, Chappy, after
Chris's time is done here,

41:21.817 --> 41:25.019
you need to find and invest
in a Chef, like Chris.

41:25.120 --> 41:27.922
There should be someone
qualified in that kitchen

41:28.023 --> 41:29.223
on a daily basis.

41:29.357 --> 41:30.657
- Absolutely.
- 'Cause it's worth it.

41:30.758 --> 41:33.359
The only thing that's gonna
keep this place on the map

41:33.460 --> 41:36.063
- is the food.
- Will do.

41:36.164 --> 41:39.099
Starr, you must make me
a very serious promise.

41:39.200 --> 41:41.101
You must not let Chappy go backwards.

41:43.304 --> 41:45.938
- I promise.
- Good.

41:46.039 --> 41:47.940
I'm only telling you
this for your own good,

41:48.041 --> 41:49.241
'cause you are one stubborn man.

41:49.275 --> 41:50.542
Good luck to you both.

41:50.643 --> 41:52.144
- Thank you so much.
- Yeah.

41:52.245 --> 41:53.979
- Thank you.
- You heard my prayer.

41:54.081 --> 41:55.581
I don't know how you did it.

41:55.682 --> 41:57.783
Thank you so much.

41:57.884 --> 41:59.384
Come here, you. Ah.

41:59.485 --> 42:01.420
- Good luck to you both. Take care.
- Thank you.

42:01.521 --> 42:02.620
- Thank you so much.
- Good night.

42:02.722 --> 42:03.822
- Good night.
- Good night.

42:07.426 --> 42:10.561
I've got one word to describe
my time here at Chappy's,

42:10.662 --> 42:12.663
and that is "challenging."

42:12.765 --> 42:16.101
Mainly because Chappy let his
restaurant slide in so many ways.

42:16.202 --> 42:19.302
But we made a major
turnaround, and he even agreed

42:19.403 --> 42:21.605
to get rid of his ridiculous chef's hat.

42:21.706 --> 42:23.540
My only hope now is that he's gotten rid of

42:23.641 --> 42:25.843
all those bad habits, because if he hasn't,

42:25.944 --> 42:28.946
this restaurant has no chance.

42:29.047 --> 42:32.082
Wow.

42:33.618 --> 42:36.385
Not long after Chef Ramsay left,

42:36.486 --> 42:38.420
in spite of positive
feedback about the changes,

42:38.521 --> 42:41.124
Chappy went back to his old ways.

42:41.225 --> 42:43.025
You didn't do what I asked you.

42:43.127 --> 42:44.727
I should have come behind you
and babysat you, you're right.

42:44.828 --> 42:47.663
The majority of his
original dishes are back...

42:47.765 --> 42:50.065
Blackened pork chop,
blackened swordfish on the fly.

42:50.166 --> 42:52.667
And so is the uncertainty of the future

42:52.769 --> 42:55.503
of this Nashville restaurant.

